                <h1>Combating PTSD Insomnia: Sleep Solutions</h1>
                <p>PTSD insomnia is a common symptom experienced by individuals with post-traumatic stress disorder. It manifests as difficulty falling asleep, staying asleep, or experiencing disturbing dreams. This can lead to increased anxiety and fatigue, complicating daily life. Effective strategies include therapy, relaxation techniques, and medication to improve sleep quality.</p>
